# RDF 2.0.0 Release Notes

## What's New
- Multi-tool adapter architecture: Gemini CLI, Codex, and cross-tool AGENTS.md
- `rdf generate gemini-cli` produces .gemini/agents/*.md + .gemini/commands/*.toml
- `rdf generate codex` produces AGENTS.md + .codex/config.toml for Codex CLI
- `rdf generate agents-md` produces cross-tool AGENTS.md (<150 lines)
- `rdf generate all` invokes all four adapters in sequence
- `rdf refresh` command with memory, plan, and github scopes
- EM (mgr.md) uses rdf-state JSON for 60-78% token savings at startup
- `/reload` displays context anchor block (project/branch/version/dirty)
- Cross-project context drift fix at session start (Friction Fix 4)
- Canonical-first architecture — all content is tool-agnostic markdown
- {domain}-{role} naming convention across all agents and commands
- Unified `rdf` CLI with generate, sync, state, and github subcommands
- Claude Code adapter: canonical + metadata-driven YAML frontmatter generation
- Deterministic `rdf state` helper — project JSON in <1s, no LLM
- GitHub Issues + Projects v2 integration (labels, projects, custom fields)
- 4-profile system: core, systems-engineering, security, frontend
- Self-verification gates in QA and Sentinel (addresses false-positive friction)
- Scope confirmation in EM/mgr (addresses wrong-scope friction)
- Plugin manifest (.claude-plugin/plugin.json)
- Agent Teams dispatch abstraction (`rdf dispatch`) with dual-mode support
  (subagent default, Agent Teams opt-in via RDF_AGENT_TEAMS=true)
- Centralized agent registry and pipeline task templates with dependency chains
- Agent Teams research, dispatch specification, and coordination mapping docs

## Breaking Changes
- workforce/ directory renamed to rdf/
- All agent CC names changed (rfxn-se -> rfxn-sys-eng, etc.)
- All persona slash commands changed (/se -> /sys-eng, etc.)
- /root/.claude/{commands,agents,scripts} are now symlinks to adapter output
- /root/.claude/ is now a deployment target — develop in rdf/canonical/

## Migration
1. Run `bin/rdf generate claude-code`
2. Back up existing /root/.claude/{commands,agents,scripts}
3. Create symlinks: `ln -sf .../adapters/claude-code/output/{dir} /root/.claude/{dir}`
4. Remove overwatch-hook.sh from settings.json SubagentStop hooks
See README.md for full migration instructions.
